atest edition of the Greek text. About the first edition: "The best [English version] we are likely to see for some time."--James Merrill, The New York Review of Books "[Keeley and Sherrard] have managed the miracle of capturing this elusive, inimitable, unforgettable voice. It is the most haunting voice I know in modern poetry."--Walter Kaiser, The New Republic ?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPOETRY / European / General.2bisacsh  aALEXANDRIAN KINGS.  aAN OLD MAN.  aBEFORE TIME ALTERED THEM.  aCANDLES.  aCOME BACK.  aDAYS OF 1896.  aDAYS OF 1908.  aEXILES.  aFOR THE SHOP.  aGRAY.  aHALF AN HOUR.  aHE SWEARS.  aIMENOS.  aIN CHURCH.  aIN SPARTA.  aIONIC.  aKAISARION.  aLONG AGO.  aLONGINGS.  aMONOTONY.  aNERO'S DEADLINE.  aON THE STAIRS.  aOROPHERNIS.  aPICTURED.  aPOSEIDONIANS.  aSIMEON.  aTHE AFTERNOON SUN.  aTHEODOTOS.  aTHINGS ENDED.  aUNDERSTANDING.  aVOICES.1 aKeeley, Edmund.1 aSavidis, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSherrard, Philip.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691213132zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691213132423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691213132.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK